HEADWORD: Monitorial
<hw>Mon`i*to"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to a monitor or monitors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Done or performed by a monitor; <as>as,
<ex>monitorial</ex> work</as>; conducted or taught by monitors; <as>as,
a <ex>monitorial</ex> school; <ex>monitorial</ex>
instruction.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monitorially</ent>⟦br⟧
